### Writing AI-Friendly Code
When writing or suggesting code:
1. Use explicit, descriptive names (see `docs/AI_FRIENDLY_CODE.md`)
2. Add documentation comments explaining *why*, not *what*
3. Include usage examples for complex functions
4. Make error messages actionable with context
5. Use type aliases for clarity
6. Follow established patterns from `docs/COMMON_PATTERNS.md`
